Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All parameters are within normal limits except for elevated creatinine (2.7 mg/dL), indicating impaired renal function. Electrolytes, liver enzymes, proteins, and lipid profile are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease and assessment of renal function trend. No acute metabolic or hepatic abnormalities detected.
